<head><title>
	Nucor - Nucor Reports Results for the First Quarter of 2026
</title><meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="Content-type" /><meta content="RevealTrans(Duration=0,Transition=0)" http-equiv="Page-Enter" /><meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" /><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" name="viewport" /><meta content="default-src &#39;self&#39; https: http: data: &#39;unsafe-inline&#39; &#39;unsafe-eval&#39; *.q4inc.com *.q4cdn.com; script-src &#39;self&#39; *.bootstrapcdn.com *.datatables.net *.cloudfront.net *.pusherapp.com *.newrelic.com *.nr-data.net *.bugherd.com *.q4cdn.com *.q4web.com *.amazonaws.com *.highcharts.com *.googletagmanager.com *.googleadservices.com *.google-analytics.com *.google.com *.gstatic.com *.q4app.com *.fonts.net *.pendo.io https://acsbapp.com &#39;unsafe-inline&#39; &#39;unsafe-eval&#39; *.q4inc.com" http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" /><meta content="q8va2Tv0rwPb7cMHzuleFCUoaatYj--qb0MsTQIDwXo" name="google-site-verification" /><meta content="Nucor Reports Results for the First Quarter of 2026" property="og:title" /><meta name="description" content="Nucor Corporation (NYSE: NUE) today announced consolidated net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders of $743 million, or $3.23 per diluted share, for the first quarter of 2026. Nucor reported consolidated net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders in the fourth quarter of 2025 of $378 million, or $1.64 per diluted share (adjusted net earnings of $400 million, or $1.73 per diluted share). Nucor reported net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders in the first quarter of 2025 of $156 million, or $0.67 per diluted share (adjusted net earnings of $179 million, or $0.77 per diluted share). &quot;Nucor teammates delivered a strong start to 2026, with our steel mills segment achieving a new quarterly shipment record,&quot; said Leon Topalian, Nucor&#39;s Chair and Chief Executive Officer. &quot;All three of our operating segments reported sequential earnings growth, driven by strong demand across key end markets, growing contributions from recent capital investments, and federal trade policies" property="og:description" /><meta content="website" property="og:type" /><meta content="https://investors.nucor.com/news/news-details/2026/Nucor-Reports-Results-for-the-First-Quarter-of-2026/default.aspx" property="og:url" /><meta name="twitter:title" content="Nucor Reports Results for the First Quarter of 2026" /><meta name="twitter:description" content="Nucor Corporation (NYSE: NUE) today announced consolidated net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders of $743 million, or $3.23 per diluted share, for the first quarter of 2026. Nucor reported consolidated net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders in the fourth quarter of 2025 of $378 million, or $1.64 per diluted share (adjusted net earnings of $400 million, or $1.73 per diluted share). Nucor reported net earnings attributable to Nucor stockholders in the first quarter of 2025 of $156 million, or $0.67 per diluted share (adjusted net earnings of $179 million, or $0.77 per diluted share). &quot;Nucor teammates delivered a strong start to 2026, with our steel mills segment achieving a new quarterly shipment record,&quot; said Leon Topalian, Nucor&#39;s Chair and Chief Executive Officer. &quot;All three of our operating segments reported sequential earnings growth, driven by strong demand across key end markets, growing contributions from recent capital investments, and federal trade policies" /><!--[if lte IE 8]>
